cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.AI 

The paper introduces a deep learning model to learn continuous-time dynamics on complex networks and infer the semantic labels of nodes in the network at terminal time. The paper involves the use of neural networks and optimization techniques to solve the problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the dynamics of complex systems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the use of differential equations, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with graph semi-supervised classification tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
